<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="note 2">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note 2.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
As recorded in the synonymy section preceding Note 1, 
<taxonomicName class="Gastropoda" family="Sinuspiridae" genus="Michelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Michelia platypetala" order="Pleurotomariida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="platypetala">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Michelia platypetala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is noted as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. cavaleriei" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="cavaleriei">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">M. cavaleriei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and has been made a variety of both 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dunn (Figlar) var. rubicunda (T. P. Yi &amp; J. C. Fan) C. B. Callaghan &amp; S. K. Png" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Dunn (Figlar) var. rubicunda (T. P. Yi &amp; J. C. Fan) C. B. Callaghan &amp; S. K. Png" baseAuthorityYear="2020" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Magnoliaceae" genus="Magnolia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Magnolia maudiae" order="Magnoliales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="maudiae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Magnolia maudiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Gastropoda" family="Sinuspiridae" genus="Michelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Michelia cavaleriei" order="Pleurotomariida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="cavaleriei">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Michelia cavaleriei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the 2001 and 2008 publications with a noted elevational range of 1200-1500 m despite 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Handel-Mazzetti’s">Handel-Mazzetti's</normalizedToken>
type collection being made at ca. 950 metres. However, 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. platypetala" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="platypetala">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">M. platypetala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
retains its species status in 
<bibRefCitation author="Law, YW" journalOrPublisher="Acta Phytotaxonomica Sinica" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" publicationUrl="http://frps.iplant.cn/" refId="B48" refString="Law, YW, Lo, HS, Wu, YF, Chang, BN [Eds], 1996. Magnoliaceae. In: Flora Reipublicae Popularis Sinicae Tomus 30(1) Angiospermae, Dicotyledoneae: Menispermaceae, Magnoliaceae. Science Press, Beijing, 82-273. http://frps.iplant.cn/" title="Magnoliaceae. In: Flora Reipublicae Popularis Sinicae Tomus 30 (1) Angiospermae, Dicotyledoneae: Menispermaceae, Magnoliaceae. Science Press, Beijing, 82 - 273." url="http://frps.iplant.cn/" year="1996">Law et al. (1996</bibRefCitation>
: 177), 
<bibRefCitation author="Liu, YH (Law YW)" journalOrPublisher="Baitong Group, Beijing Science &amp; Technology Press, Beijing" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B55" refString="Liu, YH (Law YW), Zeng, QW, Zhou, RZ, Xing, FW [Eds], 2004. Magnolias of China. Baitong Group, Beijing Science &amp; Technology Press, Beijing" title="Magnolias of China." year="2004">Liu et al. (2004</bibRefCitation>
: 306), 
<bibRefCitation author="Sima, YK" journalOrPublisher="PhD Thesis, Yunnan University, Kunming" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" publicationUrl="http://www.docin.com/p-1050989203.html" refId="B71" refString="Sima, YK, 2011. A Taxonomic Revision of the Magnoliaceae from China. PhD Thesis, Yunnan University, Kunming, http://www.docin.com/p-1050989203.html" title="A Taxonomic Revision of the Magnoliaceae from China." url="http://www.docin.com/p-1050989203.html" year="2011">Sima (2011</bibRefCitation>
: 219), 
<bibRefCitation author="Deng, LX" journalOrPublisher="Guizhou Science and Technology Publishing House, Guiyang" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B20" refString="Deng, LX, Yang, XY, 2015. Guizhou Magnoliaceae Plants. Guizhou Science and Technology Publishing House, Guiyang" title="Guizhou Magnoliaceae Plants." year="2015">Deng and Yang (2015</bibRefCitation>
: 144) and 
<bibRefCitation author="Yang, KM" journalOrPublisher="Science Press, Beijing" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B86" refString="Yang, KM, Chen, XL, Gong, X, Wang, YL [Eds], 2016. Ex Situ Cultivated Flora of China : Magnoliaceae. Science Press, Beijing" title="Ex Situ Cultivated Flora of China: Magnoliaceae." year="2016">Yang et al. (2016</bibRefCitation>
: 306).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="note 3">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note 3.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<bibRefCitation author="Grimshaw, J" journalOrPublisher="International Dendrology Society / Kew Publishing, Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B34" refString="Grimshaw, J, Bayton, R, 2009. New Trees-Recent Introductions to Cultivation. International Dendrology Society/ Kew Publishing, Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew" title="New Trees-Recent Introductions to Cultivation." year="2009">Grimshaw and Bayton (2009</bibRefCitation>
: 500) record a personal communication received from Richard Figlar in 2007 advising that &quot;this taxon (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sima" authorityYear="2001" baseAuthorityName="Hand. - Mazz." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Magnoliaceae" genus="Magnolia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Magnolia maudiae subsp. var. var. platypetala" order="Magnoliales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="maudiae" subSpecies="var." variety="platypetala">Magnolia maudiae var. platypetala</taxonomicName>
) probably ought to be recognised at the specific level, as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C. B. Callaghan &amp; S. K. Png" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="C. B. Callaghan &amp; S. K. Png" baseAuthorityYear="2020" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Magnoliaceae" genus="Magnolia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Magnolia platypetala" order="Magnoliales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="platypetala">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Magnolia platypetala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as it differs considerably from 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. maudiae" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="maudiae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">M. maudiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
both in its hairiness and its later bud-break&quot;. 
<bibRefCitation author="Sima, YK" journalOrPublisher="PhD Thesis, Yunnan University, Kunming" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" publicationUrl="http://www.docin.com/p-1050989203.html" refId="B71" refString="Sima, YK, 2011. A Taxonomic Revision of the Magnoliaceae from China. PhD Thesis, Yunnan University, Kunming, http://www.docin.com/p-1050989203.html" title="A Taxonomic Revision of the Magnoliaceae from China." url="http://www.docin.com/p-1050989203.html" year="2011">Sima (2011</bibRefCitation>
: 327), illustrates the contrasting difference between the indumentum of the undersurfaces of the leaves of 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. platypetala" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="platypetala">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">M. platypetala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Plate 3-4H) and that of the leaves of 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. maudiae" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="maudiae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">M. maudiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Plate 3-4C). Additionally, in a study by 
<bibRefCitation author="Zhang, XH" journalOrPublisher="Acta Phytotaxonomica Sinica" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="167 - 190" publicationUrl="http://www.plantsystematics.com/CN/article/downloadArticleFile.do?attachType=PDF&amp;id=225" refId="B88" refString="Zhang, XH, Xia, NH, 2007. Leaf architecture of subtribe Micheliinae (Magnoliaceae) and its taxonomic significance. Acta Phytotaxonomica Sinica 45 (2): 167 - 190, http://www.plantsystematics.com/CN/article/downloadArticleFile.do?attachType=PDF&amp;id=225" title="Leaf architecture of subtribe Micheliinae (Magnoliaceae) and its taxonomic significance." url="http://www.plantsystematics.com/CN/article/downloadArticleFile.do?attachType=PDF&amp;id=225" volume="45" year="2007">Zhang and Xia (2007)</bibRefCitation>
on leaf architecture and its taxonomic significance in respect of subtribe 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Y.W.Law" authorityYear="1984" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="subTribe" subTribe="Micheliinae">Micheliinae</taxonomicName>
of 
<taxonomicName family="Magnoliaceae" genus="M." lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="family">Magnoliaceae</taxonomicName>
, the pronounced contrast in the leaves of 
<taxonomicName class="Gastropoda" family="Sinuspiridae" genus="Michelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Michelia platypetala" order="Pleurotomariida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="platypetala">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Michelia platypetala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. cavaleriei" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="cavaleriei">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">M. cavaleriei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as revealed by stereoscopic magnified imaging (shown at figs. 36 and 37 in their paper), resulted in these authors concluding that these two taxa should be recognised as independent species&quot;. It is apparent that there is now an almost unanimous consensus of the species status of 
<taxonomicName class="Gastropoda" family="Sinuspiridae" genus="Michelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Michelia platypetala" order="Pleurotomariida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="platypetala">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Michelia platypetala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which is confirmed by the comparison of its morphological features with those of 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. cavaleriei" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="cavaleriei">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">M. cavaleriei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
compiled in Table 
<tableCitation captionStart="Table 5" captionStartId="T5" captionText="Table 5. Differentiating features of the species Michelia platypetala and M. cavaleriei." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/0F9202D236A02A5D5F1C663AE2BE68D9" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" tableUuid="0F9202D236A02A5D5F1C663AE2BE68D9">5</tableCitation>
below. In view of its distinctive characteristics and accepting the majority recognition by the above-mentioned Chinese authors of 
<taxonomicName class="Gastropoda" family="Sinuspiridae" genus="Michelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Michelia platypetala" order="Pleurotomariida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="platypetala">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Michelia platypetala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
